One node Decision Tree: Decision Stump

A Decision Stump is a one-node Decision Tree. The dataset is split on the values of as single provided attribute. The label at the leaf nodes is decided via the majority voting algorithm.

Below is the example of decision stump. The attribute is  "anaemia". The dataset is split whether a person has anemia (right) or not(left). Both the labels at the leaf nodes indicate "alive" prediction.

Please refer img folder

Prerequisite
Python 3